# Content Enhancer Loop (Strict)

Follow this loop exactly for article enhancement tasks. Stack with `content-pipeline-loop.mdc` when doing full remediation.

1. Create `temp_articles_checklist.txt` with one line per article:
   - Format: `- [ ] src/content/blog/<slug>.mdx`
2. Pick the first unchecked article.
3. Remove forbidden copy before rewrite: shared title suffix `„Ю„У„®„Щ„Ъ „Ю„Ґ„©„Щ, „©„Щ„Ш„Х„™ „Щ„Щ„©„Х„Э „Х„Ш„Ґ„Х„Щ„Х„™ „©„Ы„У„Р„Щ „Ь„Ю„†„Х„Ґ`, opening nav boilerplate `„Ы„У„Щ „Ь„С„†„Х„™ „Ф„І„©„® „®„Ч„С`, closing `„¶„≥„І„Ь„Щ„°„Ш „Ф„®„Ч„С„Ф „Ь„Щ„Щ„©„Х„Э „Ю„Щ„Щ„У„Щ`, and `## „™„Х„Ы„†„Щ„™ 30/60/90 „Щ„Х„Э` blocks.
4. Improve **title**, **metaTitle** (50вАУ60 chars), **metaDescription** (120вАУ165 chars), and **description** together; preserve `mainKeyword` from `SITE_KEYWORDS` in `src/consts.ts`.
5. Research: write `.cursor/tmp/research/<slug>.md`; translate to Hebrew; delete temp file after body merge.
6. Replace MDX body with topic-specific Hebrew prose; no body `#` H1; first `##` must not duplicate layout `title`.
7. Meet tier word minimum (pillar вЙ•1200, cluster вЙ•900, slug contracts in `scripts/lib/content-tiers.mjs`).
8. YMYL slugs: add вЙ•2 external `https://` links to authority hosts (gov.il, israelbar.org.il, etc.).
9. Run dev server and review live article.
10. Run `pnpm run content:audit` for this slug; fix failures.
11. Mark `- [x] src/content/blog/<slug>.mdx`.

Hard requirements:
- No Unicode em dash U+2014 (use `-`, `:`, commas).
- Do not set `updatedDate` unless body materially changed; never batch-stamp without `materialChange: true` in frontmatter when schema allows.
- Run `pnpm run image-keyword-compliance` if `images` changed.
- Log: `[content-enhancer-loop] step N` or `ERROR`.
- Never modify unrelated files or schema fields.
